<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910814-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>910814-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- BellSouth Corp.:   Third-Period Charge Reflects   Early Retirement Program</HL><DATE>08/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19</SO><CO>   BLS</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>TELEPHONE SYSTEMS, INCLUDING CELLULAR (TLS)</IN><RE>GEORGIA (GA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   BellSouth Corp. said it expects to take a one-time chargeagainst third-quarter earnings of about $87 million, or 18cents a share, to reflect costs of an early retirementprogram.   The regional telephone company based in Atlanta offeredearly retirement in May to about 10,600 managerial employees.It said about 3,100 managers elected to take the option andwill be retiring by Oct. 31. Another retirement optionannounced in late 1990 was taken by about 1,150 managers.</LP><TEXT>   In the year-earlier third quarter, BellSouth had netincome of $402.9 million, or 84 cents a share.   The company said it expects to begin to receive savingsfrom the voluntary program in the fourth quarter and that thebenefits will continue in 1992 and beyond.</TEXT></DOC>